1. Using tcpdump explain connection termination in tcp with appropriate packets.

2. ifconfig shows MTU size. Try setting buffer size greater than that for respective interfaces; and show how data transmission takes place. Read mannual pages of tcp and udp. 

3. Explore the optional data in tcp header.

4. Explore about netstat command.
How you can see all listening ports, all active connections, all kernel routing information, disable dns lookup?

5. How selective ack can be send? and how you can debug it?

6. What /proc/sys/net/ipv4/tcp_wmem and /proc/sys/net/ipv4/tcp_rmem tells about?

7. Make client server communicating on UDP.

8. Make concurrent echo server which can serve multiple clients simultaneously. 

9. Make daytime server where client requests day time and server sends current day time in appropriate formate to client.  

10. Explore following networking APIs or structures and make one demo application out of all.

socket(), bind(), connect(), close(), getaddrinfo(), freeaddrinfo(), gai_strerror(), gethostname(), gethostbyname(), gethostbyaddr(), getservbyname(), getnameinfo(), getpeername(), errno, fcntl(), htons(), htonl(), ntohs(), ntohl(), inet_ntoa(), inet_aton(), inet_addr, addrinfo, inet_ntop(), inet_pton(), listen(), perror() , strerror(), poll(), recv(), recvfrom(), select(), setsockopt(),  getsockopt(), send(), sendto(), shutdown(), hostent

11. Explore netstat, traceroute, tcpdump and nmap command with all switches.
